Thanks for the additional details in your bug report: https://github.com/jOOQ/jOOQ/issues/13957

As of jOOQ 3.17.2, there seems to be a bug when using associative arrays of objects in jOOQ as procedure/function `IN` parameters. They&#39;re currently only supported as `OUT` parameters. I.e. a type like this:

```sql
create type o as object (n number);
create package p as
  type t is table of o index by pls_integer;
  procedure p (t t);
end p;
/
```

